(266, 'Biology', 'Biology is a one-credit, year-long course for freshmen students.  In addition to learning about the organization, processes and systems of life, emphasis will be placed on understanding the scientific process and developing both critical thinking and problem solving skills that will prepare students to become independent inquirers and equip them for success in future high school science courses.  Strategies for teaching this course include laboratory investigations, journaling, individual readings, graphic organizers, note-taking and summarizing, model construction, group and partner discussions, and both individual and group research projects.', 'c9057e572c', 0, 0, 1, '2011-06-10 23:46:15', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '34724.png'),
