(1, 'Open source is a development methodology,[1] which offers practical accessibility to a product\\''s source (goods and knowledge). Some consider open source as one of various possible design approaches, while others consider it a critical strategic element of their operations. Before open source became widely adopted, developers and producers used a variety of phrases to describe the concept; the term open source gained popularity with the rise of the Internet, which provided access to diverse production models, communication paths, and interactive communities.', 8, 1, 5, 0, '2011-06-10 23:58:08'),
