(35, 'Welcome to Class-Connect! \r<br />\r<br />I hope you find this resource to be both helpful and user friendly. In order to view class notes, course materials, and other important information please click on &quot;Shared Content&quot;. If you are interested in seeing a calendar of assignments and upcoming exams or quizzes, please view the course calendar above the Shared Content link. \r<br />\r<br />Please let me know if you have any questions or suggestions by writing on this comment wall. Thank you for using Class-Connect!\r<br />', 718, 1, 230, 0, '2011-06-10 23:58:08'),
(36, 'Welcome to physics class at THS! \r<br />\r<br />Science courses were switched this past Monday, so I will be your teacher instead of Mr. Yeager.  Today we discussed the syllabus and classroom expectations. The first thing students are expected to do upon entering the classroom are to read the objectives written on the whiteboard and to complete the warm-up prompt.  Students created a business card to describe and introduce themselves to both their classmates and Mr. Kern.  Students then took a pre-assessment to determine what they currently know and understand about measurement, calculations, the process of science and motion.   Lab safety contracts should be signed and turned in no later than next Tuesday (08/24).\r<br />\r<br />Enjoy your first week. \r<br />\r<br />Mr. Kern', 70, 1, 261, 0, '2011-06-10 23:58:08'),
(37, 'Welcome to IB Bio II!\r<br />\r<br />Welcome to biology class at THS! \r<br />\r<br />Today we discussed the syllabus and classroom expectations. The first thing students are expected to do upon entering the classroom are to read the objectives written on the whiteboard and to complete the warm-up prompt. Students created a business card to describe and introduce themselves to Mr. Kern. Students then took a pre-assessment to determine what they currently know and understand about last years and this year''s curriculum. Lab safety contracts should be signed and turned in no later than next Tuesday (08/24). \r<br />\r<br />Enjoy your first week. \r<br />\r<br />Mr. Kern', 70, 1, 263, 0, '2011-06-10 23:58:08'),
(38, 'Reminder: Periods 1 and 4 will probably meet in room 404 next week.  Period 8 will continue meeting in room 415.  Any changes will be posted on a sign below the 404 sign and on the sign outside of 415.', 70, 1, 261, 0, '2011-06-10 23:58:08'),
(39, 'We began the period by introducing ourselves and what each of us are most proud of (moment, accomplishment, possession, etc.).  Next, we went to the website Class Connect  (classconnect.com), signed up for an account and added our class.  Finally, we took a multiple intelligence (MI) test to identify our intelligence strengths, graph our MI profile and plan how to use this information to our advantage.\r<br />\r<br />Have a great weekend.', 70, 1, 261, 0, '2011-06-10 23:58:08'),
(40, 'Hellew! I will need help soon :D thanks', 1329, 1, 261, 0, '2011-06-10 23:58:08'),
(41, 'We opened class by discussing the homework that is due next week (adding this course to your ClassConnect account and completing the My Multiple Intelligences assignment).  I also showed students where the link to the MI survey could be found (in Shared Content).  Then, students did 2 separate quick writes about stability.  We discussed the essential questions and big ideas for the Ecology &amp; Conservation Biology unit and then watched about 19 min. of the video earth 2100.  The purpose of watching the video was to review content from last year and to consider the essential questions, big ideas and quick write responses in the context of the information presented.  We''ll probably finish watching the video next week, but  I did post a link to the earth 2100 website if you''re interested in exploring more of the content.\r<br /> \r<br />Have a great weekend!', 70, 1, 263, 0, '2011-06-10 23:58:08'),
