(19, 6, 64, 52, 'Programming TV''s for Channel One with Remote', 'Programming 19” Gray <br>Channel One Televisions<br><br><br>•&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Use either the Total Remote used at installation, or a universal remote programmed for a Phillips Magnavox television. <br><br><br>To Program follow these directions: <br><br>1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Turn on the television and adjust the volume. <br>2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Enter the programming code 05 76 97 like you are entering three different channels. (Note: Ignore “Channel 5 not available” “Channel 76 not available” “Channel 97 not available”)<br>3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Press Display/Menu<br>4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Accumulated Runtime will show on the screen. This just lets you know how many minutes Ch1 has shown on this TV. <br>5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Press Display/Menu<br>6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Channel One Enable should be highlighted in yellow. <br>7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The Phillips One channel should be either 3 or 4, depending on what Channel your site views Channel One. (If a TV is autostarting on the wrong channel usually the Phillips One channel is set to the wrong channel). <br>8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Picture: adjust as needed using +/-<br>9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Brightness: adjust as needed using +/- <br>10.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Color: adjust as needed using +/-<br>11.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tint: adjust as needed using +/-<br>12.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Sharpness: adjust as needed using +/-<br>13.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cable Tuning: Select Cable Tuning if your cable channels go over Channel 15. <br>14.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Channel Add/Delete: Select a channel with by pressing in the number, or using the up/down buttons on the remote. To add the channel to the TV’s memory, press the + or – button and select CH ADD. To delete the channel from the TV’s memory, press the + or – button and select CH DELETE. The channel will then appear in red.&nbsp; If the + or - button on your remote control does not work to make changes, you will need to use the Volume up or down on the TV to make changes.<br>15.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Exit: Press the Status/Exit key to exit the menu.&nbsp; <br><br>', '', '', '', '', '2009-05-22 05:21:18'),
