(195, 6, 118, 148, 'Elements to Know Review Sheet', '<DIV class=Section1>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: center; mso-pagination: none" align=center><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><U><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Arial'',''sans-serif''"><FONT color=#000000>Atomic Symbols<?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" /><o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></U></B></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: center; mso-pagination: none" align=center><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><U><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Arial'',''sans-serif''"><o:p><SPAN style="TEXT-DECORATION: none"><FONT color=#000000>&nbsp;</FONT></SPAN></o:p></SPAN></U></B></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-pagination: none"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Arial'',''sans-serif''"><FONT color=#000000>The following is a list of 50 chemical elements whose atomic symbols you are to memorize. Atomic symbols are the alphabet of chemistry. You will use these all year, so learn them now and review them periodically. You will be quizzed and tested over these. The elements are listed alphabetically, but do not memorize them in this order as they will be scrambled on the quizzes. Also, you must be able to write the symbol, given the name of the element, as well as be able to write the name of the element, given the symbol. <B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal">Spelling does count</B>. <o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-pagination: none"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Arial'',''sans-serif''"><o:p><FONT color=#000000>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-pagination: none"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Arial'',''sans-serif''"><FONT color=#000000>There are rules governing atomic symbols:<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-pagination: none"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Arial'',''sans-serif''"><o:p><FONT color=#000000>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; mso-pagination: none"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: ''Arial'',''sans-serif''"><FONT color=#000000>1. There is one and only one correct symbol for each element.<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; mso-pagination: none"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: ''Arial'',''sans-serif''"><FONT color=#000000>2. No two different elements may have the same symbol.<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; mso-pagination: none"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: ''Arial'',''sans-serif''"><FONT color=#000000>3. If the symbol for an element is a single letter, it <B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal">must</B> be <B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal">capitalized</B>.<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; mso-pagination: none"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: ''Arial'',''sans-serif''"><FONT color=#000000>4. If the symbol for an element is two letters, the first <B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal">must</B> be <B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal">capitalized</B>, and the second <B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal">must</B> be <B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal">lower</B><o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; mso-pagination: none"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: ''Arial'',''sans-serif''"><FONT color=#000000><SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal">case</B>.<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; mso-pagination: none"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: ''Arial'',''sans-serif''"><FONT color=#000000>5. For elements with two-letter symbols, the letters are usually those heard when the name of the element is<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; mso-pagination: none"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: ''Arial'',''sans-serif''"><FONT color=#000000><SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN>pronounced.<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; mso-pagination: none"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: ''Arial'',''sans-serif''"><FONT color=#000000>6. Some symbols do not seem related to the names of their elements. These are elements that have been <o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; mso-pagination: none"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: ''Arial'',''sans-serif''"><FONT color=#000000><SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN>known to man for a long time, and their original names were in Latin or Greek. Examples are aurum <o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; mso-pagination: none"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: ''Arial'',''sans-serif''"><FONT color=#000000><SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN>(Au) for gold, ferrum (Fe) for iron, and natrium (Na) for sodium.<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; mso-pagination: none"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: ''Arial'',''sans-serif''"><o:p><FONT color=#000000>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; mso-pagination: none"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: ''Arial'',''sans-serif''"><o:p><FONT color=#000000 size=3>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; mso-pagination: none"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: ''Arial'',''sans-serif''"><o:p><FONT color=#000000 size=3>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></SPAN></P></DIV><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Arial'',''sans-serif''; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><BR style="PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE: auto; mso-break-type: section-break" clear=all></SPAN>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; mso-pagination: none"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: ''Arial'',''sans-serif''"><o:p><FONT color=#000000 size=3>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; mso-pagination: none"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Arial'',''sans-serif''"><FONT color=#000000>1. aluminum<SPAN style="mso-tab-count: 3">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN>26. lithium<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in -0.7in 0pt 0.5in; mso-pagination: none"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Arial'',''sans-serif''"><FONT color=#000000>2. antimony<SPAN style="mso-tab-count: 3">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN>27. magnesium<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in -0.7in 0pt 0.5in; mso-pagination: none"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Arial'',''sans-serif''"><FONT color=#000000>3. argon<SPAN style="mso-tab-count: 3">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&n