(726, 277, 56, 0, '<P align=left><FONT size=3>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cobalt</FONT></P>\r\n<P align=left><FONT size=2>1.Ekkehard Schwab wrote the essay about cobalt. He was interested because cobalt had undergone a significant transformation from an \\"ugly duckling\\" of no interesting to miners into a \\"swan\\" of strategic industrial importance.</FONT></P>\r\n<P align=left><FONT size=2>2. Cobalt is used in alloys for magnets, in ceramics, in catalysts, and in paint. It is also used in magnetic and stainless steels.</FONT></P>\r\n<P align=left><FONT size=2>3. Cobalt is in 4th row, in transition metals group, and it is normally found in the state of metals.</FONT></P>\r\n<P align=left><FONT size=2>4. The intersting fact is that the word \\"cobalt\\" is derived from \\"Kobold\\", the name of a mischievious goblin in Germain mytholigy who loved to tease humans.</FONT></P>\r\n<P align=left><FONT size=2>5. This element is not dangerous in normal exposure quantities.</FONT></P>\r\n<P align=left>6. Pure cobalt is not found in nature, but compounds of cobalts are found.&nbsp;It&nbsp;is found in the minerals cobaltite, erythrite, and smaltite. It is commonly mixed with ores of iron, nickel, silver, lead, and copper. <FONT size=3></P></FONT>\r\n<P align=left><FONT size=3>&nbsp;</P></FONT>', '2009-10-09 11:53:20'),
(602, 408, 51, 0, '<P>1.&nbsp; Because solor flares erupt it can knock out satiilites and bring down power grids</P>\r\n<P>2.&nbsp; Mr. Watts helps to further understand about solor flares and how do predict them. Mr. Gekelman has a huge plasma stucture machine that can help other scientist understand plasma better. </P>\r\n<P>3.&nbsp; So you can know the threat of them and take pre cuations to prevent them.</P>\r\n<P>4.&nbsp; Because of the energy plasma produces by nuclear fusion.</P>\r\n<P>5. Yes, i thnk the understanding of plasma is necessary because of the power of it. It can affect our liifes in many ways and it could be our next potential major energy source. <BR></P>', '2009-09-27 15:35:43'),
(603, 300, 51, 0, '<font class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" face=\\"arial\\"><span class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" style=\\"font-size: small;\\">1.&nbsp;</span></font><span class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: normal; \\"><font class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" face=\\"arial\\"><span class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" style=\\"font-size: small;\\">If a solar flares erupt, massive ejections of plasma known as the solar wind can wipe out satellite systems and bring down power grids</span></font></span><div><font class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" color=\\"#000000\\" face=\\"arial, Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\\"><span class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" style=\\"font-size: small; line-height: normal;\\"><br></span></font><div><font class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" color=\\"#000000\\"><span class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" style=\\"line-height: normal; \\"><font class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" face=\\"arial\\"><span class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" style=\\"font-size: small;\\">2.&nbsp;</span></font><font class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" face=\\"arial\\"><span class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" style=\\"font-size: small;\\">Mr. Watts is building a machine that will hopefully help to illuminate the mechanisms underlying solar flares and understand them better.&nbsp;</span></font><span class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" style=\\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 18px; \\"><font class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" face=\\"arial\\"><span class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" style=\\"font-size: small;\\">Mr. Gekelman has an even larger plasma sturcture that helps him and other scientists study plasma more closely, especially the waves in plasma.</span></font></span></span></font></div><div><font class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" face=\\"arial, Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\\"><span class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" style=\\"font-size: small;\\"><br></span></font></div><div><font class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" face=\\"arial\\"><span class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" style=\\"font-size: small;\\">3. Solar flares can be dangerous and in order to protect against them, you have to first understand how they work.&nbsp;</span></font></div><div><font class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" face=\\"arial, Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\\"><span class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" style=\\"font-size: small; line-height: 19px;\\"><br></span></font></div><div><span class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" style=\\"line-height: 15px; \\"><font class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" face=\\"arial\\"><span class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" style=\\"font-size: small;\\">4. Plasmas play a large role in large scale power production, nuclear fission.&nbsp;</span></font></span></div><div><font class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" face=\\"arial, Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\\"><span class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" style=\\"font-size: small; line-height: 15px;\\"><br></span></font></div><div><span class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" style=\\"line-height: 15px; \\"><font class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" face=\\"arial\\"><span class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" style=\\"font-size: small;\\">5. It\\''s very necessary so we can protect ourselves against its danger and learn how to use it for energy purposes.&nbsp;</span></font></span></div></div>', '2009-09-27 17:20:58'),
(604, 391, 50, 0, '<P><BR>1. Understanding will help us look ahead and can warm and prevent power outs and damage.</P>\r\n<P>2. Mr. Watts said we couldn\\''t prevent them but can save the satellites and grids and My. Gekelman said \\"If we are ever going to have viable fusion power plants we have to understand how plasmas behave and how to control them.\\"</P>\r\n<P>3.&nbsp; Understanding solar flares are important because it could later be dectectable and can more satillete from the flares if you might know where they will be going.</P>\r\n<P>4. It is one of the alternatives once fossil fuels have ran out.</P>\r\n<P>5. I think plasma knowledge is necessary for scientist if they prefer to study it and can turn it into something that can help the world in the future.</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P>Austin 4th period</P>', '2009-09-27 17:41:38'),
(605, 250, 49, 0, 'The understanding of plasma is important to the communications field because so many disturbances are caused by it, such as the power outtage in Quebec. Mr. Watts has created a machine that will both produce and contain plasma. Mr. Gekelman also created a plasma-producing machine in which he studies the waves that occur in plasma. Understanding solar flares may help us to block out, or better prepare for an erruption of a solar flare that may affect satellites or grids. This will drastically improve the problems that occur in the communications field. When fossil fuels are depleted,&nbsp;nuclear fusion, which includes plasma,&nbsp;may be&nbsp;one of the only large-scale power sources we will be able to use.&nbsp;Personally, I believe that improving our knowledge on plasma is necessary. Although working in nuclear power plants and creating nuclear fusion can be extremely dangerous, if only professionals are in charge of dealing with it, it will not be as great of a danger. If we can further understand plasma, we can also help prevent solar flares that affect people of the world.<BR>', '2009-09-27 17:48:15'),
(606, 311, 47, 0, '1. &nbsp;When there are solar flares, plasma can ruin the satellite systems or destroy power grids. &nbsp;If they understood plasma, then they could predict when the solar flares would occur.<div>2. &nbsp;Mr. Watts has been building a machine that will hopefully understand the mechanisms of solar flares. &nbsp;Mr. Gekelman has made a machine that creates plasma so he can study its waves, etc.</div><div>3. &nbsp;Understanding solar flares is important because if we understand them, then we can predict them and avoid having satellite systems destroyed or extreme power outages.</div><div>4. &nbsp;Once the fossil fuels run out, plasma will be used in nuclear fusion to create power.</div><div>5. &nbsp;I think it is&nbsp;necessary&nbsp;because if we know more about plasma, then we can avoid serious damages and have a backup for when we run out of fossil fuels. &nbsp;</div>', '2009-09-27 18:29:06'),
(607, 309, 50, 0, '<ol><li>Understanding plasma can help with the power outages and even provide power in the future when fossil fuel runs out.</li><li>Mr. Watts is contributing by trying to protect the satellites and power lines. Mr. Gekelman is contributing by try to figure out how to used the plasma as a power source.</li><li>Understanding it could give us technology in the future to power our cities, etc.</li><li>It could very well be the source of our energy production.</li><li>I believe its necessary. If we get to the point that we can use plasma as a energy source i believe it will be very beneficial to us.</li></ol>Daniel Kim 4th period<br>', '2009-09-27 18:48:44'),
