latin;\r\n	mso-fareast-font-family:\\"Times New Roman\\";\r\n	mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;\r\n	mso-hansi-font-family:Calibri;\r\n	mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]-->\r\n\r\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\">Jora Zaidi</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\">Hollis</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\">Chemistry 2<sup>nd</sup></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\">September 28, 2009</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"text-align: center;\\" align=\\"center\\">Forum: The Fourth\r\nState of Matter</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\">Question 1: The understanding of plasma is important to the\r\ncommunications field, because of the affect of solar flares. Solar flares are\r\nheld accountable for wiping out satellite systems, and bringing down power\r\ngrids. <br>\r\n<br>\r\nQuestion 2: Contributions made by Mr. Watts and Mr. Gekelman are as follows:\r\nMr. Watts has been building a machine in which he hopes will illuminate the\r\nmechanisms underlying solar flares; Mr. Gekelman has made a larger machine\r\nsimilar to Mr. Watts for the same purpose.<br>\r\n<br>\r\nQuestion 3: The understanding of solar flares is important, because of the\r\nknowledge gained from its affects on the Earth, and in the solar system. <br>\r\n<br>\r\nQuestion 4: Plasma might affect energy production in the world once fossil\r\nfuels are depleted, because of nuclear fusion. Nuclear fusion is one of the few\r\nalternatives for large scale power production.<br>\r\n<br>\r\nQuestion 5: Improved plasma knowledge is necessary<span style=\\"\\">&nbsp; </span>to further the experimentation on the usage\r\nof alternative energy when fossil fuels are depleted. Since I am an\r\nenvironmentalist, the alternative method for consuming energy by using plasma\r\nwould be a more environmentally cautious decision. </p>', '2009-09-28 14:59:06'),
(615, 402, 51, 0, '<P><BR><FONT face=helvetica>1. When solar flares erupt, massive ejections of plasma known as the solar wind can wipe out satellite systems and bring down power grids. if we knew more about these explosions and how to predict them, then we would be able to protect our satellites and grids. also plasmas may also play a central role in meeting future energy needs. when fossil fuels run out, one of the few alternatives for large scale power production is neculear fusion. \\"if we are ever going to have viable fusion power plants we have to understand how plasmas behave and how to control them.\\" (Walter Gekelman)</FONT></P>\r\n<P><FONT face=helvetica></FONT>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P><FONT face=helvetica>2. Mr. Watts has been building a machine that he hopes will help to illuminate the mechanisms underlying solar flares.</FONT></P>\r\n<P><FONT face=helvetica>With a super-quiet plasma&nbsp;Mr Gekelman&nbsp;is able to study the exotic kinds of waves which occur in this medium, some of which don\\''t occur anywhere else in nature.</FONT></P>\r\n<P><FONT face=helvetica></FONT>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P><FONT face=helvetica>3. because then we will be able to predict when they will happen and protect our satellites and grids.</FONT></P>\r\n<P><FONT face=helvetica></FONT>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P><FONT face=helvetica>4.&nbsp;when fossil fuels run out, the alternative for large scale power production will be nuclear fusion. and in order to use it, we need to be able to understand how it works so we can control it.</FONT></P>\r\n<P><FONT face=helvetica></FONT>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P><FONT face=helvetica>5. since 99% of visible stuff in our universe is&nbsp;in the&nbsp;form of plasma. i think that knowledge about it is very necessary. it will also play a key role in meeting future energy needs, there for we need to learn as much about it as possible in order to properly use it.</FONT></P>', '2009-09-28 17:38:20'),
(616, 401, 51, 0, '<P><STRONG><FONT size=2 face=arial>1. </FONT><SPAN style=\\"FONT-FAMILY: \\''Tahoma\\'', \\''sans-serif\\''; COLOR: black; FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \\''Times New Roman\\''; mso-font-kerning: 18.0pt\\"><FONT size=2><FONT face=arial>Understanding plasma is important because when solar flares erupt, massive ejections of plasma known as the solar wind can wipe out satellite systems and bring down power grids.</FONT></FONT></SPAN></STRONG></P>\r\n<P><STRONG><SPAN style=\\"FONT-FAMILY: \\''Tahoma\\'', \\''sans-serif\\''; COLOR: black; FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \\''Times New Roman\\''; mso-font-kerning: 18.0pt\\"><FONT size=2><FONT face=arial></FONT></FONT></SPAN></STRONG>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P><STRONG><SPAN style=\\"FONT-FAMILY: \\''Tahoma\\'', \\''sans-serif\\''; COLOR: black; FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \\''Times New Roman\\''; mso-font-kerning: 18.0pt\\"><FONT size=2><FONT face=arial>2. Mr. Watts has been building a machine to illuminate the mechanisms underlying solar flares, and Mr. Gekelman has become an expert on generating striations.</FONT></FONT></SPAN></STRONG></P>\r\n<P><STRONG><SPAN style=\\"FONT-FAMILY: \\''Tahoma\\'', \\''sans-serif\\''; COLOR: black; FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \\''Times New Roman\\''; mso-font-kerning: 18.0pt\\"><FONT size=2 face=Arial></FONT></SPAN></STRONG>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P><STRONG><SPAN style=\\"FONT-FAMILY: \\''Tahoma\\'', \\''sans-serif\\''; COLOR: black; FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \\''Times New Roman\\''; mso-font-kerning: 18.0pt\\"><FONT size=2 face=Arial>3. Understanding solar flares is important because when they erupt, they fling charged particles into space where they form a solar wind. This solar wind messes with the magnetic field of the Earth.</FONT></SPAN></STRONG></P>\r\n<P><STRONG><SPAN style=\\"FONT-FAMILY: \\''Tahoma\\'', \\''sans-serif\\''; COLOR: black; FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \\''Times New Roman\\''; mso-font-kerning: 18.0pt\\"><FONT size=2 face=Arial></FONT></SPAN></STRONG>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P><STRONG><SPAN style=\\"FONT-FAMILY: \\''Tahoma\\'', \\''sans-serif\\''; COLOR: black; FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \\''Times New Roman\\''; mso-font-kerning: 18.0pt\\"><FONT size=2 face=Arial>4.&nbsp; Once fossil fuels are depleted, plasma can be used in large scale production to form nuclear power. </FONT></SPAN></STRONG></P>\r\n<P><STRONG><SPAN style=\\"FONT-FAMILY: \\''Tahoma\\'', \\''sans-serif\\''; COLOR: black; FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \\''Times New Roman\\''; mso-font-kerning: 18.0pt\\"><FONT size=2 face=Arial></FONT></SPAN></STRONG>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P><STRONG><SPAN style=\\"FONT-FAMILY: \\''Tahoma\\'', \\''sans-serif\\''; COLOR: black; FONT-SIZE: 10.5pt; mso-fareast-font-family: \\''Times New Roman\\''; mso-font-kerning: 18.0pt\\"><FONT size=2 face=Arial>5. Yes improved knowledge about plasma is necessary. We use plasma everyday and should be aware of what we are working with for our safety. </FONT></SPAN></STRONG></P><BR>', '2009-09-28 17:48:51'),
(617, 399, 49, 0, '<BR>Understanding the importance of plasma for the communication field is very important because if a solar flare erupts then it could wipe out satelitte and bring down power grinds and this could leave us without power or communication till fixed so if we understand we will know what prcautions we need to take. Mr. Watts and Mr. Gekelman hae contributed machines that can similuate plasma and solar flares therefore it will allow us to go into deeper studies about plasma and how it works. UNderstanding solar flares are important because it can lead us to figuring out symptons of what might cause the flare to explod and how long it will take so we could in the future monitor them and find out when they will explode so we can build protection around our satellites. IT might provide a new and possibly better power source that we could use and since we know how to make it then we will have a never ending power source. YEs it is necessary because it will help us not only know how to protect our satellites and power grinds but it will help us learn more about solar flares and it could help us find a better power source to use rather than fossil fuels or electrcity.', '2009-09-28 18:36:20'),
(618, 304, 47, 0, '<P>1. Understanding plasma is important to the communications field, becase it can cause major disruptions in satelites and power outages on earth without warning when they arrive in the form of solar winds. This is slightly hazardous to us today considering how much we rely on phones, computers, and satelites to relay information, but if we understand them than we may be able to avoid these occurances.</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P>2. Mr. Watts created a machine that contains streams of plasma, making it easy to study in a laboratory environment. Mr. Gekelman\\''s machine generates large quantities of plasma, allowing him to observe the Alven waves as they move along the plasma collums.</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P>3. Like I said in my fist aswer, solar winds (which are produced by solar flares) can take down satelites and power grids when they comeincontact with earth, understanding these phenomena can help us avoid the solar flares before they hit.</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P>4. Plasma has an infinite number of potential uses, including enery. By the time that&nbsp;fossil fules run out, most likely we will have discovered ways to harness the power of plasma, and it can be used in place of fossil fules.</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P>5. Of course, it\\''s necessary many ways, such as the reasons mentioned earlier and for all the other possible ways it\\''s enery could be understood and harnessed. Some might not consider that completely necesary, but I believe that we should still try to learn more about it for discovery\\''s sake. There is so much of it around us in so many different places and appearances that it seems that learning and discovering more about it would be something that most scientitsts would want achieve.</P>', '2009-09-28 18:48:04'),
