(623, 333, 50, 0, '<P>1. Understanding plasma for the communcation feild is important because , when solar flares erupt, massive ejections of plasma can wipe out satellite systems and bring down power grids.</P>\r\n<P>2. Mr. Watts&nbsp;was building a machine that&nbsp;will hopefully&nbsp;illuminate the mechanisms underlying solar flares, and Mr. Gekelman is trying to understand how plasa behaves and how to control plasma.</P>\r\n<P>3. Behing able to understand solar flares is important because with out understanding them we will not be able to protect our satellites from being destroyed by the solar flares.</P>\r\n<P>4. we may be able to use plasma as our main source of energy once we have used all our fossil fuels.</P>\r\n<P>5. I believe that further knowledge of plasma maybe necessary for the future, because it could be very helpful in the furure and could be used as one of our main resources in the near future.</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P>-Kristen Keown<BR></P>', '2009-09-30 11:58:51'),
(624, 351, 47, 0, '<P><FONT face=georgia>1.The understanding of plasma is important to the communication fields because when satellites systems&nbsp;are wiped out by solar flares&nbsp;it can disturb the use of cell phones.</FONT></P>\r\n<P><FONT face=Georgia>2. Mr. Watts and Mr. Gekelman both&nbsp;built machines in hopses of&nbsp;understanding&nbsp;more about&nbsp;plasma.</FONT></P>\r\n<P><FONT face=Georgia>3. Solar flares are important to understand because they create solar winds which mess the planets magentic field when they pass by.</FONT></P>\r\n<P><FONT face=Georgia>4. Once fossil fuels are depleted plasma might affect the energy production by being used as nuclear fusion.</FONT></P>\r\n<P><FONT face=Georgia>5. Improved knowledge on plasma is necessary because of how&nbsp;plasma affects the planet and the possiablity of it being used for energy.</FONT></P>\r\n<P><FONT face=Georgia></FONT>&nbsp;</P>', '2009-09-30 17:01:29'),
(625, 297, 49, 0, '<P>1. It is important to understand plasma when in the communications field, because plasma makes up solar flares, with have been known to tamper with cellphone signals, other satellite signals, and power lines. </P>\r\n<P>2. Mr. Watts and Mr. Gekelman have created machines that can hold plasma and Mr. Watts\\''s machine is helping research how solar flares work. Both machines may contribute to the harnessing of plasma.</P>\r\n<P>3. Understanding solar flares is important, because they can cause problems here on earth (as shown in 1.). If we know more about solar flares, we can predict them, and take measures to save our satelites and powerlines which are sometimes damaged during solar flares.</P>\r\n<P>4. Many scientists believe that after fossil fuels are depleted, we can use plasma in fusion power plants as an alternate source of energy.</P>\r\n<P>5. Improved plasma knowledge is very important, because it can lead to better protections of power grids, and increased knowledge about plasma, it could serve as a source of energy.</P>\r\n<P><BR>&nbsp;</P>', '2009-10-01 13:15:16');
