e>\r\n<![endif]-->\r\n\r\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\">1) Studying the plasma has become very inportant because\r\nsolar flares erupt, massive ejection of plasma known as the solar winds can\r\ndamage and completely wip out satellite systems and bring down power grids.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n2) Mr. Watts is in the process of making a machine which he hopes will help\r\nilluminate the mechanisms underlying solar flares and Mr. Gekelman is also\r\nbuilding a machine that is larger than Mr. Watts creating a super quiet plasma<br>\r\n<br>\r\n3) If a solar flare erupt, charging particles can be thrown into the space\r\nwhere they may form solar winds and this solar winds can warp Earth\\''s magnetic\r\nfield.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n4) If fossil fuel does run out there are only a few things that we can use. One of the few things for a large scale power production is nuclear fusion.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n5) I think it is important to improve plasma knowledge because plasma may help\r\nus in the future.</p>', '2009-10-01 18:01:16'),
(627, 317, 51, 0, '<P><BR>1. The understanding of plasma is important to the communications field because when solar flares erupt, the solar wind can wipe out satellite systems and power grids.</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P>2. Mr. Watts is building an 18 foot long michine hoping it will help illuminate the mechanisms underlying solar flares, and Mr. Gekelman has also built a machine 22 meters long. Mr. Gekelman has become an expert at generating striations and plasma structures.</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P>3. Understanding solar flares is important because plasmas are a mixture of charged particles and those motions in a plasma can make circulating streams of electrical current. When solar flares erupt, charged particles are thrown out into space where they form the solar wind, which can take down power grids. Solar flares can also distort magnetic fields.</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P>4. If fossil fuels are depleted, the alternative for plasmas in large scale power production is nuclear fission.</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P>5. Having plasma knowledge is necessary because it can help us in the future protect ourselves from the wiping out of satellite systems and power grids, and it could be used for energy purposes.</P>', '2009-10-01 20:08:40'),
(628, 365, 49, 0, '<P>1. Understanding plasma is important to te communications field because there is a threat of erupting solar flares which cause large ejections of plasma known as solar wind. These ejections of plasma are dangerous because they can bring down satellite systems and power grids. If this happens it can leave us in a state without power or communication.</P>\r\n<P>2. Mr. Watts has been working on a machine that could help illuminate the mechanisms underlying solar flares. Mr. Gekelman has been able to build a machine 22 meters in length that generates plasma, and this machine is free from background noise. Inside his machine he can produce different kinds of plasma waves and measure the three-dimensional movement of the magnetic field surrounding them.</P>\r\n<P>3. Understanding solar flares is important because if you understanding what is causing solar flares you might be able to predict when they will occur which will give you time to protect any power grids or satellites that could be effected by the solar wind. </P>\r\n<P>4. Once fossils fuels are depleted, one of the few large-scale sources for power is from nuclear fusion. In order to have viable nuclear fusion plants, you need to understand how to control plasma.</P>\r\n<P>5.Improved plasma knowledge is necessary because it will save millions of dollars if we are able to predict when solar flares will erupt causing the solar wind that harms our satellites and power grids, and if we understand plasma even more than we do now we will be able to have successful nuclear fusion plants to generate energy at a very large scale which could solve our energy crisis.<BR></P>', '2009-10-02 07:23:28'),
(629, 404, 50, 0, '<P>&nbsp;1. Solar flares/solar winds, which are made of plasma, often bombard the earth with their radiation. They can destroy satellites, interfere with communication systems such as cell phones, and throw off electrical circuits on the surface of the earth. If we can better understand plasmas, then we have a better chance of finding a way to protect these commodities from any more interferences.</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P>2. Both of these men have created machines that can properly contain plasma. They hope to use these machines and the plasma they create as research tools to better our understanding of plasma.</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P>3. Understanding solar flares is the first step towards protecting our satellites and communications systems from their harmful effects</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P>4. Some scientists hope that we can eventually harness the energy created by plasma to be used as fuel.</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P>5. Improving our knowledge of plasma is not absolutelynecessary, but it&nbsp;would certainly&nbsp;be helpful. In&nbsp;a world which&nbsp;is totally dependant on a dwindling supply of fossil fuels, a new energy source is vital to the survival of the modern society that we know of today, and plasma could be the&nbsp;permanent solution that we need. We cannot afford to overlook it or brush it to the side as just another wild theory. It is&nbsp;definitely something worth taking a more in-depth look at.</P>', '2009-10-02 12:06:09'),
(630, 335, 47, 0, '<P>1.&nbsp;Understanding plasma is important to the communications field because&nbsp;plasma comes from solar flares , known as solar wind,&nbsp;&nbsp;and causes great damage to power grids and satellite systems. The damages to the power grids and satellite systems can cause a power outage to earth or even a huge storm. Sometimes, our cell phones even stop workig. If we knnew about plasma, we could stop some of the damage by moving the satellites.</P>\r\n<P>2. Mr. Watts and Mr. Gekelman both built a machine that will help them understnd more about plasma.</P>\r\n<P>3. When we understand solar flares, we know what kind of damage it makes, so we can try to stop it.</P>\r\n<P>4. When fossil fuels are depleted, we may have to use plasma as our new energy source.</P>\r\n<P>5. We do need to improve our knowledge on plasma because we can learn how to stop some of the damage it does to us and if we run out out of fossil fuel, we need to know if plasma works for sure, so we can use it.<BR></P><BR>', '2009-10-02 13:44:45'),
(631, 277, 49, 0, '<P><BR>1. Understanding the plasma is important to the communications field.&nbsp;The reason is that&nbsp;it can effect our communication because solar wind can wipe out satelite system and bring down power grits.</P>\r\n<P>2. Mr. Watts built a machine that illuminate the mechanisms underlying solar flares. Mr. Gekelman also built a machine where he can produce waves and measure the three-dimensional menoment of the magnetic field.</P>\r\n<P>3. Understanding solar flares is important because they form solar winds which distort the magnetic field surrounding our planet.</P>\r\n<P>4. Nuclear fusion is one of the few alternatives when fossil fuels are depleted.</P>\r\n<P>5. I think improved plasma knowledge&nbsp;is necessary because events dealing with plasma affect our everyday life. So, studying about plasma can help us prepare for future events.</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>', '2009-10-02 15:21:22'),
(632, 339, 50, 0, '<P><BR><FONT face=\\"courier new\\">1. Plasmas may play a central role in meeting future energy needs.</FONT></P>\r\n<P><FONT face=\\"Courier New\\"></FONT>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P><FONT face=\\"Courier New\\">2. Mr. Watts built a machine that he hopes will help to illuminate the mechanisms underlying solar flares. Mr. Gekelman became an expert at generating striations and other, even more exotic plasma structures. </FONT></P>\r\n<P><FONT face=\\"Courier New\\"></FONT>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P><FONT face=\\"Courier New\\">3. Because when they erupt, massive ejections of plasma known as the solar wind can wipe out satellite systems and bring down power grids.</FONT></P>\r\n<P><FONT face=\\"Courier New\\"></FONT>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P><FONT face=\\"Courier New\\">4. Scientists who dream of clean and endless fusion power are slowly learning how to harness and control extremely hot plasmas. If such efforts bear practical fruit the effect on the world\\''s energy economy would be profound.</FONT></P>\r\n<P><FONT face=\\"Courier New\\"></FONT>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P><FONT face=\\"Courier New\\">5. Yes because the more we find out and the more we understand plasma, the more we can use it in our world.</FONT></P>', '2009-10-02 16:05:00'),
(633, 349, 49, 0, '<P class=MsoNormal style=\\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\\"><FONT size=1><FONT face=arial><SPAN style=\\"COLOR: #333333; FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma\\">I think the understanding of plasma is important to the communications field because it is located all over the world but we didn’t even know it. In the form of ionized gas, that is also part of the fourth state of matter, is contained in lightning, flames, auroras, and every florescent tube. Also because these huge flames of plasma, called solar winds, are known to wipe out many important devices on earth such as power lines, cell phone towers, satellite systems and tower grids. </SPAN></FONT></FONT><FONT size=1><FONT face=arial><SPAN style=\\"COLOR: #333333; FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma\\">Mr. Watts says that if they were able to predict when the solar winds would happen, they’d be able to protect the satellites and power grids.</SPAN><FONT color=#000000> </FONT><SPAN style=\\"FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma\\"><FONT color=#000000>He has been building a machine, at New Mexico Tech, that he hopes will help to clarify solar flares and this mechanism he’s built need to have a magnetic field stronger than the sun and the Earth just to keep the plasma contained in this device. Mr. Gekelman says that it’s almost as if the plasma were alive because it breaks apart and reconnects, in a snake-like form, in the pattern to make it seem as if they are “rebuilding” their community. His creation is significantly bigger in size compared to Mr. Watts and it is “shaped like a giant caterpillar, it can produce a continuous volume of plasma about 56 feet long”.</FONT><SPAN style=\\"COLOR: #333333\\"> Understanding solar flares is important because they will hopefully be able to predict when the next solar flare will happen to attempt to protect our instruments here on Earth from the extremely hot temperatures. They are hoping that when we run out of fossil fuels, then nuclear fusion, which is one of only a few choices, is our alternative for large scale power production. I believe the knowledge of plasma is very important to learn more about because fossil fuels are rapidly depleting and we need a back up plan. Also to understand the behavior of the solar flares up on the sun so we will have hopes of protecting our satellites and power grids. This was a very interesting article because I learned a lot of stuff about plasma that I had never known before. <?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = \\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office\\" /><o:p></o:p></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></P><BR>', '2009-10-03 06:18:30'),
