ns */\r\n table.MsoNormalTable\r\n	{mso-style-name:\\"Table Normal\\";\r\n	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\n	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\r\n	mso-style-parent:\\"\\";\r\n	mso-padding-alt:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin:0in;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:10.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\\"Times New Roman\\";}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]-->\r\n\r\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"margin-left: 0.5in; text-indent: -0.25in;\\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\\"font-family: Impact; color: rgb(51, 204, 0);\\"><span style=\\"\\">1)<span style=\\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal; -x-system-font: none;\\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\\"font-family: Impact; color: rgb(51, 204, 0);\\">Massive\r\nejections of plasma, known as solar winds, can knock down satellite systems and\r\nbring down&nbsp;power&nbsp;grids during the occurrence of solar flares.<br>\r\n<br style=\\"\\">\r\n<!--[endif]--><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"margin-left: 0.5in; text-indent: -0.25in;\\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\\"font-family: Impact; color: rgb(51, 204, 0);\\"><span style=\\"\\">2)<span style=\\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal; -x-system-font: none;\\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\\"font-family: Impact; color: rgb(51, 204, 0);\\"><span style=\\"\\">&nbsp;</span>Mr. Watts proposes the idea that if we learn\r\nmore about solar flares than even though we cannot stop them from happening, we\r\ncan predict when they\\''re coming and prepare for them; he is also in the process\r\nof constructing an 18 foot long machine in hopes that it will help illuminate\r\nmechanisms underlying the solar flares. Mr. Gekelman is also in the process of\r\nconstructing a machine; however, his is 22 meters long and can produce\r\ncontinuous volume of plasma about 56 feet long. This plasma is super quiet\r\nwhich enables him to study exotic kinds of waves occurring in this medium, with\r\nsome that don’t occur any where else in nature.</span></p><p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"margin-left: 0.5in; text-indent: -0.25in;\\"><br><span style=\\"font-family: Impact; color: rgb(51, 204, 0);\\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"margin-left: 0.5in; text-indent: -0.25in;\\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\\"font-family: Impact; color: rgb(51, 204, 0);\\"><span style=\\"\\">3)<span style=\\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal; -x-system-font: none;\\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\\"font-family: Impact; color: rgb(51, 204, 0);\\">Understanding\r\nsolar flares is important because when a solar flare erupts, charged particles\r\nfly into space creating solar winds. When the particles from the solar wind\r\nfling back toward earth, the solar wind distorts the Earth’s surrounding\r\nmagnetic field, stretching the field lines hundreds of thousands of miles. When\r\nthe lines are over distorted, they snap back even closer into Earth’s\r\natmosphere.</span></p><p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"margin-left: 0.5in; text-indent: -0.25in;\\"><br><span style=\\"font-family: Impact; color: rgb(51, 204, 0);\\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"margin-left: 0.5in; text-indent: -0.25in;\\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\\"font-family: Impact; color: rgb(51, 204, 0);\\"><span style=\\"\\">4)<span style=\\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal; -x-system-font: none;\\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\\"font-family: Impact; color: rgb(51, 204, 0);\\">When\r\nwe run out of fossil fuels, nuclear fission will be one of the only few\r\nalternatives for large scale power production so plasma needs to be studies so\r\nwe can watch how it behaves and control it.</span></p><p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"margin-left: 0.5in; text-indent: -0.25in;\\"><br><span style=\\"font-family: Impact; color: rgb(51, 204, 0);\\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\\"MsoNormal\\" style=\\"margin-left: 0.5in; text-indent: -0.25in;\\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\\"font-family: Impact; color: rgb(51, 204, 0);\\"><span style=\\"\\">5)<span style=\\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal; -x-system-font: none;\\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\\"font-family: Impact; color: rgb(51, 204, 0);\\">Yes,\r\nI believe improved plasma knowledge is necessary because understanding how to\r\nuse is can give clues to the working of stars and effect the world’s energy\r\neconomy to help us in the future with new technologies and uses of plasma.<o:p></o:p></span></p>', '2009-10-03 09:13:08'),
