(652, 413, 47, 0, '<P><BR><FONT face=arial size=2>1. The understanding of plasma is important to the communications field because&nbsp;when solar flare erupt solar winds can whip out satellite systems and bring down power grids.</FONT></P>\r\n<P><FONT face=Arial size=2>2. Mr. Watts and Mr. Gekelman both constructed machines to help understand solar flares.</FONT></P>\r\n<P><FONT face=Arial size=2>3. Understanding solar flares in important because we would be able to predict them and help prevent damage to satellite systems and power grids.</FONT></P>\r\n<P><FONT face=Arial size=2>4.&nbsp;When fossil fuels are depleted we can use plasma as an energy source.</FONT></P>\r\n<P><FONT face=Arial size=2>5. </FONT>&nbsp;I believe it is necessary to impove our knowledge on plasma to prevent damage to satellites and so when our fossil fuels do eventually burn out we have something we can rely on as an energy source.</P>', '2009-10-04 13:00:48'),
(653, 345, 48, 0, '<P><BR>1: Solar flares are important to understand in the communications field because solar flares erupt causing wipe outs of satellites and bring down power grids.</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P>2:Mr. Watts contributed by making a machine that would immitate solar flares.&nbsp; This would help with the study and understanding of them.&nbsp; Mr. Gekelman built the machine only larger.&nbsp; The machine serves the same purpose.</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P>3:It is important to study solar flares becuase when we study them we can figure out ways to cope with the effects of the such as how they cause solar winds.&nbsp; Learning from these can reduce the risk of damages of the satellites.</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P>4: Plasma will contribute once fossil fuels are depleted by supplying the world with large amounts of energy for everyday usage.</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P>5:Improved knowledge of plasma is necessary because it will give us energy we can use to supply the world with energy and it is great knowledge for future generations; they could do so much with knowledge we have today.</P>', '2009-10-04 13:12:30'),
(654, 356, 50, 0, '<P>1. Understanding plasma is important because massive ejections of plasma known as the solar wind can wipe out satellite systems and bring down power grids.<BR></P>\r\n<P>2. They built a machine&nbsp;that&nbsp;will help to illuminate the mechanisms underlying solar flares. </P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P>3. Understang sloar flares are important because a huge solar flare left six million people in Quebec without power and&nbsp;in 1998 a flare was blamed for a daylong disturbance to millions of cellphone customers.</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P>4.<FONT face=\\"Courier New\\"> Scientists who dream of clean and endless fusion power are slowly learning how to harness and control extremely hot plasmas. </FONT></P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P><FONT face=\\"Courier New\\">5.&nbsp;improved plasma knowledge is necessary&nbsp;because the more&nbsp;people find out about plasma&nbsp;and also&nbsp;the more we understand plasma, the more we can use it in our everyday lives.</FONT></P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>', '2009-10-04 13:28:22'),
(655, 363, 47, 0, '1.) Understanding plasma is important to the communications field because erupting solar flares (large discharges of plasma) can destroy satellite and power systems worth millions of dollars.<br><br>2.) Watts and Gekelman both built machines that attempt to learn more about solar flares / plasma.<br><br>3.) If we can understand solar flares, we can avoid having our satellite systems and power grids being destroyed by them. <br><br>4.) Once fossil fuels are depleted, plasma may have to fill the void in terms of energy production.<br><br>5.) Yes. With additional research and development, we can effectively predict / prevent the massive damage that solar flares can cause.&nbsp; We could also find a way to efficiently be able to harvest the energy that plasma can supply.<br>', '2009-10-04 13:33:37'),
(656, 265, 49, 0, '<BR>\r\n<P><FONT face=\\"Times New Roman\\" color=#000000 size=3>1) The understanding of plasma is important to the communications field because when solar flares erupt,&nbsp;masses of plasma ejects and causes damage to satellites and effects the power in millions of homes.</FONT></P>\r\n<P><FONT face=\\"Times New Roman\\" color=#000000 size=3>2) Mr. Watts knows that we can\\''t stop the flares from erupting but we can try to predict them to save the satellites and prevent these problems in the future. He has created a machine in attempt to capture the plasma which is a major problem to scientists. Mr. Gekelman says that we must understand how plasma behaves and works in order to fusion power plants.</FONT></P>\r\n<P><FONT face=\\"Times New Roman\\" color=#000000 size=3>3) It is important to understand solar flares because they cause the solar wind that affects the magnetic field of the earth and has the ability to wipe out satellites. </FONT></P>\r\n<P><FONT face=\\"Times New Roman\\" color=#000000 size=3>4) If scientists&nbsp;continue&nbsp;studying how to control hot plasma, it&nbsp;could possibly be used as a source of energy when fossil fuels are gone.</FONT></P>\r\n<P><FONT face=\\"Times New Roman\\" color=#000000 size=3>5) Yes, I think it is necessary because it can potential be harmful and also helpful in the future. Either way, it is very important to know what plasma is, how it behaves, and how we can control it. If this is accomplished, we can possibly use plasma as a resource of energy and prevent future power loss.</FONT></P>', '2009-10-04 13:46:11'),
(657, 258, 48, 0, '<P class=MsoNormal style=\\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt\\"><SPAN style=\\"FONT-SIZE: 9pt; COLOR: #333333; LINE-HEIGHT: 115%; FONT-FAMILY: \\''Tahoma\\'',\\''sans-serif\\''\\"><FONT face=georgia color=#ff6699><FONT size=2><STRONG><U><FONT color=#336699 size=3>1.</FONT></U>Communications is so important in today’s world. Everyone operates from their cell phone or their blackberry or laptop. When something causes our gadgets not to work properly, we feel helpless. One of these causes is solar flares, which produce enormous ejections of plasma also known as solar winds. They have the strength to wipe out entire satellite systems and knock down power grids.<SPAN style=\\"mso-spacerun: yes\\">&nbsp; </SPAN>The more scientists learn about plasma, the better we can protect our satellite systems and power grids from these solar winds.&nbsp; </STRONG></FONT></FONT></SPAN><FONT face=georgia color=#ff6699 size=3></P>\r\n<P><FONT color=#000000><FONT size=+0><FONT face=georgia><FONT size=1><STRONG><SPAN style=\\"FONT-SIZE: 9pt; COLOR: #333333; LINE-HEIGHT: 115%; FONT-FAMILY: \\''Tahoma\\'',\\''sans-serif\\''\\"><FONT face=georgia><FONT size=2><U><FONT color=#ff6699 size=3>2.</FONT></U></FONT></FONT></SPAN><FONT color=#003399>Mr. Watts and Mr. Gekelman have both built a massive machine that they hope will allow them to better understand plasma, a state of matter that until now has been somewhat of a mystery to physicists. Down at New Mexico Tech, Mr. Watt’s machine can generate a magnetic field believed to be much larger that even the sun’s and can produce plasma from a process called ionization of argon atoms. Not only does he hope to highlight the mechanisms or solar flares, but also be able to model the process of magnetic reconnections using his machine. Over at U.C.L.A., Mr. Gekelman houses a machine in his facility that is even larger that Mr. Watts. He and some of his colleagues can expertly generate striations and even more exotic structures of plasma. Since he is experimenting with super-quiet plasma, he has the ability to research exotic waves which occur in this special medium, and some of which do not appear anywhere else in nature. <SPAN style=\\"mso-spacerun: yes\\">&nbsp;</SPAN></FONT></STRONG></FONT></FONT></FONT></FONT></P><SPAN style=\\"FONT-SIZE: 9pt; COLOR: #333333; LINE-HEIGHT: 115%; FONT-FAMILY: \\''Tahoma\\'',\\''sans-serif\\''\\">\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style=\\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt\\"><SPAN style=\\"FONT-SIZE: 9pt; COLOR: #333333; LINE-HEIGHT: 115%; FONT-FAMILY: \\''Tahoma\\'',\\''sans-serif\\''\\"><FONT size=2><STRONG></STRONG></FONT></SPAN>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style=\\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt\\"><SPAN style=\\"FONT-SIZE: 9pt; COLOR: #333333; LINE-HEIGHT: 115%; FONT-FAMILY: \\''Tahoma\\'',\\''sans-serif\\''\\"><FONT size=2><STRONG><FONT color=#ff6699><SPAN style=\\"FONT-SIZE: 9pt; COLOR: #333333; LINE-HEIGHT: 115%; FONT-FAMILY: \\''Tahoma\\'',\\''sans-serif\\''\\"><FONT face=georgia color=#ff6699><FONT size=2><STRONG><U><FONT color=#336699 size=3>3.</FONT></U></STRONG></FONT></FONT></SPAN>When we are able to understand solar flares, we are able to protect our environment from their negatives affects and also understand other phenomenon in nature such as auroras, which are very similar to solar flares. </FONT></STRONG></FONT></SPAN></P><SPAN style=\\"FONT-SIZE: 9pt; COLOR: #333333; LINE-HEIGHT: 115%; FONT-FAMILY: \\''Tahoma\\'',\\''sans-serif\\''\\"><FONT size=2><FONT color=#ff6699><?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = \\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office\\" /><o:p>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style=\\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt\\"><SPAN style=\\"FONT-SIZE: 9pt; COLOR: #333333; LINE-HEIGHT: 115%; FONT-FAMILY: \\''Tahoma\\'',\\''sans-serif\\''\\"><STRONG><SPAN style=\\"FONT-SIZE: 9pt; COLOR: #333333; LINE-HEIGHT: 115%; FONT-FAMILY: \\''Tahoma\\'',\\''sans-serif\\''\\"><FONT face=georgia><FONT size=2><U><FONT color=#ff6699 size=3>4.</FONT></U></FONT></FONT></SPAN><FONT color=#003399>Once we use up all of the fossil fuels, one of the only alternatives for power production on a large scale is nuclear fusion. Physicists like Walter Gekelman believe that knowing about plasma and how to control it is the only way we are ever going to have viable fusion power plants. <o:p></o:p></FONT></STRONG></SPAN></P></o:p></FONT></FONT></SPAN>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style=\\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt\\"><SPAN style=\\"FONT-SIZE: 9pt; COLOR: #333333; LINE-HEIGHT: 115%; FONT-FAMILY: \\''Tahoma\\'',\\''sans-serif\\''\\"><STRONG><SPAN style=\\"FONT-SIZE: 9pt; COLOR: #333333; LINE-HEIGHT: 115%; FONT-FAMILY: \\''Tahoma\\'',\\''sans-serif\\''\\"><FONT face=georgia color=#ff6699><FONT size=2><STRONG><U><FONT color=#336699 size=3>5.</FONT></U></STRONG></FONT></FONT></SPAN><FONT color=#ff6699>I believe that improved plasma knowledge is necessary because the effects of plasma could greatly affect our everyday lives. If solar winds were to hit my town, power might be out for days. Schools and offices would have to close because their computers would not be working. Television is not only a source of entertainment, that‘s also where we get updates on news and weather. If we can’t get that information from the internet or the television, where do we get it from? No one has hand held radios anymore. And if we can’t use our cell phones due to interference with the satellite, we can’t reach each other easily if we’re apart. Plasma knowledge could save our lives in my opinion.</FONT></STRONG></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style=\\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt\\"><STRONG><BR></STRONG></P></SPAN>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style=\\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt\\"><STRONG></STRONG>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P><FONT face=\\"Times New Roman\\" color=#000000><U></U></FONT></FONT>&nbsp;</P>', '2009-10-04 14:00:59'),
(658, 357, 49, 0, '<OL>\r\n<LI>\r\n<DIV>Communications are important because when solar flares blow up, massive amounts of plasma, which is the solar wind can wipe out satellite systems and bring down power grids. If they knew more, thwy could prevent the devastion. </DIV></LI>\r\n<LI>\r\n<DIV>Mr. Watts is builing a machine that is cylinderacal and is surrounded by electromagnetic coils. He hopes it will \\"illuminate the mechanisms underlying solar flares\\". Mr. Gekelman machine is very large. It fills a football -sized field lab at UCLA. It can produce a contious volume of plasma 56 ft long. </DIV></LI>\r\n<LI>\r\n<DIV>It is believed that the magnetic tearing and reconnection is what produces solar flares. It may also be what heats the corona of the sun.This hits close to home. </DIV></LI>\r\n<LI>\r\n<DIV>Plasma might be one of our olny hopes of a large scale energy source. </DIV></LI>\r\n<LI>\r\n<DIV>Improved plama knowledge is neccesary. Well all need to be informed about whats going on on our planet. If we want to help with the situation, we need to stay informed.</DIV></LI></OL>', '2009-10-04 14:11:26'),
