(660, 376, 47, 0, '<P>1. The understanding of plasma is important to the communications feild because when solare flares erupt massive ejections called solar winds can wipe out satellite systems and bring down power grids.<BR></P>\r\n<P>2. Both of the scientists have built machines that will help them understand solar flares/plasma better.</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P>3. The understanding of solar flares is important so that we can possible predict when they are coming and then prevent them from happening and messing up our satellite systems and power grids.</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P>4. Plasma will help because once fossil fuels run we will have to resort to another resource for energy which is plasma.</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P>5. Yes, becuase it could be one of are future sources of energy which is very important.</P>', '2009-10-04 15:53:47'),
(661, 406, 51, 0, '<P><BR><FONT color=#ff9933 size=1 face=verdana><STRONG>1. The Understanding of&nbsp;plasma is important because when solar flares erupt, massive ejections of plasma can wipe out satellite systems and bring down power grids. </STRONG></FONT></P>\r\n<P><FONT color=#ff9933 size=1 face=verdana><STRONG><U><EM></EM></U></STRONG></FONT>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P><FONT color=#ff9933 size=1 face=verdana><STRONG>2.<FONT>Mr. Watts has been building a machine that he hopes will help to illuminate the mechanisms underlying solar flares and help to </FONT>further understand about solor flares and how do predict them. Mr. Gekelman has a huge plasma stucture machine that can help other scientist understand plasma better. </STRONG></FONT></P>\r\n<P><FONT color=#ff9933 size=1 face=verdana><STRONG><U><EM></EM></U></STRONG></FONT>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P><STRONG><FONT size=1><FONT color=#ff9933 face=verdana>3. understanding solar flares is important because when a solor flare erupts charged particles fly into space creating solar winds</FONT></FONT></STRONG></P>\r\n<P><FONT color=#ff9933><STRONG><FONT size=1 face=Verdana></FONT></STRONG><SPAN style=\\"FONT-FAMILY: Impact; COLOR: rgb(51,204,0)\\"><FONT size=1 face=verdana><STRONG><U><EM></EM></U></STRONG></FONT></SPAN></FONT>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P><SPAN style=\\"FONT-FAMILY: Impact; COLOR: rgb(51,204,0)\\"><FONT size=1><FONT color=#ff9933 face=verdana><STRONG>4.Once fossil fuels are depleted, plasma can be used in large scale production to form nuclear power. </STRONG></FONT></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P><SPAN style=\\"FONT-FAMILY: Impact; COLOR: rgb(51,204,0)\\"><STRONG><EM><U><FONT color=#ff9933 size=1 face=Verdana></FONT></U></EM></STRONG></SPAN>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P align=left><SPAN style=\\"FONT-FAMILY: Impact; COLOR: rgb(51,204,0)\\"><FONT color=#000000 face=Arial><FONT size=2><STRONG><FONT color=#ff9933 size=1 face=verdana>5. yes, </FONT><FONT color=#333333 face=Helvetica><FONT color=#ff9933 size=1 face=verdana>since 99% of visible stuff in our universe is&nbsp;in the&nbsp;form of plasma i think it is important.</FONT> </FONT></STRONG></FONT></FONT></SPAN></P>', '2009-10-04 16:33:29'),
(662, 340, 49, 0, '<P><FONT size=2>1. Understanding plasma is very important in the area of communications because when solar flares erupt, solar wind, which is a large ejection of plasma, can demolish satellites and power grids. If scientists had no knowledge of plasma, then solar flares would end up causing a lot more damage because satallites and grids could not be protected.</FONT></P>\r\n<P><FONT size=2></FONT>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P><FONT size=2>2. Mr. Watts has been working on a machine that will assist in illuminating the mechanisms underlying solar flares. Mr Gekelman built a machine that creates a continuous volume of plasma that stretches 56 feet. He is interested in knowing more about Alven waves. His machine produces detailed images and animations of Alven waves.</FONT></P>\r\n<P><FONT size=2></FONT>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P><FONT size=2>3. Understanding solar flares is important because the more we understand them, the better we can predict them. If we can predict solar flares, then we can protect our satellites and grids.</FONT></P>\r\n<P><FONT size=2></FONT>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P><FONT size=2>4. Plasma may affect energy production because scientists are beginning to learn how to control extremely hot plasmas to create fusion power.</FONT></P>\r\n<P><FONT size=2></FONT>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P><FONT size=2>5. It is important to improve our knowledge about plasma because scientists will be able to predict solar flares which will protect our satallites and prevent power outages. It could also create an alternate way of producing energy if all of Earth\\''s fossil fuels become depleted. </FONT></P>\r\n<P><FONT size=2></FONT>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P><FONT size=2></FONT>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P><BR></P>', '2009-10-04 16:38:52'),
(663, 336, 49, 0, '<P>1) Because solar wind knocks out the satellites and power grids, leaving people without power and cell phone use. Knowing more about it can prevent future occurances.&nbsp; </P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P>2)&nbsp; Mr. Watts created a machine that helps shine light on the underlying mechanisms of solar flares.&nbsp; By creating a magnetic field, he successfully contained plasma which is said to be one of the most difficult tasks when researching it.&nbsp; Mr. Gekelman created a machine that produces Alven waves, which he uses to make detailed images of Alven waves as they move&nbsp;through the plasma column.</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P>3)&nbsp; <FONT color=#000000 size=3 face=\\"Times New Roman\\">It is important because solar flares&nbsp;make the solar wind that effects the magnetic field of the earth and can destroy satellites and power grids.&nbsp; We can prevent this if we truely knew more about it.&nbsp; </FONT></P>\r\n<P><FONT color=#000000 size=3 face=\\"Times New Roman\\"></FONT>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P><FONT color=#000000 size=3 face=\\"Times New Roman\\">4) Knowing exactly how plasma works and behaves can lead us to creating fusion power plants which take us away from relying on fossil fuels for energy.&nbsp; </FONT></P>\r\n<P><FONT color=#000000 size=3 face=\\"Times New Roman\\"></FONT>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P><FONT color=#000000 size=3 face=\\"Times New Roman\\">5)&nbsp; It is important because so much of our universe is made up of plasma, so it\\''s a given to know everything there is about it.&nbsp; Also, it has alot of potential in the future for better and smarter energy and maybe even other uses that haven\\''t been discovered yet.&nbsp; </FONT></P>', '2009-10-04 16:47:58'),
(664, 373, 48, 0, '<P><BR>1. Understanding plasma is important to the communications field because when solar flares erupt,&nbsp;the solar wind can wipe out satellite systems and bring down power grids.</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P>2. Mr. Watts built a massive machine to help us bettrer understand plasma by the process of magnetic reconnection. Mr Gekelman\\''s machine helped quiet plasma so it would be easier for us to understand. </P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P>3. Understanding solar flares is important because it can have an impact on people and power lines and satellites. </P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P>4. Once fossil fuels are depleted one of the few alternatives for large scale power production is nuclear fusion. But as Mr. Gekelman says,&nbsp;\\"If we are ever going to have viable fusion power plants we have to understand how plasmas behave and how to control them.\\"</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P>5. Improved plasma knowlege is necessary because it has such an impact on people and someday may be used in place of fossil fuels. Its scary to think that something we know such little about may be something we have to use in an everyday life to survive.</P>', '2009-10-04 16:49:49');
