(668, 372, 48, 0, '1. Plasma is important to the communications field because when solar\r\nflare is erupt into space, it cause a solar wind. The solar wind has\r\nplasma which can wipe out satellite systems and power grids. This can\r\naffect the magnetic field and energy level. For example,in 1989 a huge solar flare left six million people in Quebec without\r\npower; in 1998 a flare was blamed for a daylong disturbance to millions\r\nof cellphone customers. <br>\r\n2. Mr. Watts and Mr. Gekelman both built machines, but Mr. Gekelman\\''s\r\nmachine was bigger than Mr. Watt\\''s. His was able to study exotic waves\r\nwhich don\\''t occur in anywhere else in nature, and Mr. Watt\\''s was about\r\nthe solar flares.<br>\r\n3. Solar flares are important to understand because it for predicting the effects of solar activity on the Earth and in space.<br>\r\n4.Once fossil fuels is run out, then our alternatives is nuclear fusion.<br>5. Plasma is necessary because we wouldn\\''t know our universe and the plasma behaviors that it can effect.<br>', '2009-10-04 17:21:57'),
(669, 407, 51, 0, '1. In the event of a solar flare eruption, huge ejections of plasma can destroy our satellite systems and bring down our power grid.<br><br>2. Mr. Watts is currently making a machine in which he intends will help to illuminate the mechanisms underlying solar flares. Mr. Gekelman has made an even larger machine that scientists use to study the waves of plasma.<br><br>3. It is important to understand them because we will then be able to predict when the next solar flare eruption will be, and then we can protect our satellite systems.<br><br>4. Plasma contributes to a lot in the making of nuclear energy. Nuclear energy can be an alternative source of energy once all the fossil fuels are used up.<br><br>5. Yes, it is very necessary because we will know how to protect ourselves against the dangers of it, and we can also use it for energy<br>', '2009-10-04 17:27:58'),
(670, 358, 47, 0, '1. &nbsp;Regarding the communications field, plasma must be understood to prevent solar winds from interfering with satellite communications and power grids.<br><br>2.&nbsp; Both scientists have created machines to better understand the effects of solar flares.<br><br>3.&nbsp; Knowledge of solar flares could help mitigate or even prevent the negative effects they cause.<br><br>4.&nbsp; By the process of nuclear fusion, plasma could become a new energy resource after fossil fuels.<br><br>5.&nbsp; I believe improved knowledge of plasma is necessary due to the increased need of new energy resources today.&nbsp; Understanding it further could also prevent the issues solar flares cause.<br>', '2009-10-04 17:29:58'),
(671, 390, 50, 0, '1) Understanding plasma can prevent it from taking out satellites and also prevent power outages. they can also interfere with cell phones and other types of communication.<div><br></div><div>2) They both built machines that can hold plasma, with hopes that it will lead to better research.</div><div><br></div><div>3) If we understand solar flares then we can better protect our satellites.</div><div><br></div><div>4) Hopefully in the future we will be able to use plasma as fuel.</div><div><br></div><div>5) I don\\''t think that plasma knowledge is important now, but in the future it definitely will because we are going to run out of fossil fuels eventually.</div>', '2009-10-04 17:39:00'),
