-family: &quot;Porky\\''s&quot;;\\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\\"font-size: 14pt;\\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: &quot;Porky\\''s&quot;;\\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: &quot;Porky\\''s&quot;;\\">4.Can be\r\nused to form nuclear power after fossil fuels are used up. </span></strong><span style=\\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: &quot;Porky\\''s&quot;;\\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\\"font-size: 14pt;\\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: &quot;Porky\\''s&quot;;\\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: &quot;Porky\\''s&quot;;\\">5. I believe it is important because it will help us understand the miracles\r\nof the sky, stars.</span></strong><span style=\\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: &quot;Porky\\''s&quot;;\\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>', '2009-10-04 17:39:34'),
(673, 353, 48, 0, '1. The understanding of plasma is becoming more important to the communications field because when solar flares erupt, large amounts of plasma known as solar wind can wipe out satellite systems and bring down power grids.<div style=\\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; \\"><br style=\\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; \\"></div><div style=\\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; \\">2. Mr. Watts built a machine that he hopes will illuminate the mechanisms underlying solar flares. Mr. Gekelman built a machine just like this but a little bigger.</div><div style=\\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; \\"><br style=\\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; \\"></div><div style=\\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; \\">3. Solar flares are important to understand because it helps protect the satellite system and power grids.</div><div style=\\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; \\"><br style=\\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; \\"></div><div style=\\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; \\">4. When fossil fuels are depleted, it will affect energy production because we will have to use nuclear fusion.</div><div style=\\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; \\"><br style=\\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; \\"></div><div style=\\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; \\">5.Yes, because it will help supply the world with energy and it will help protect our satellite systems and our power grids.</div>', '2009-10-04 17:42:24'),
(674, 411, 51, 0, '<!--StartFragment-->\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\\"><font class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" face=\\"arial\\"><span class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" style=\\"font-size: x-small;\\">1</span></font><font class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" face=\\"arial\\"><span class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" style=\\"font-size: x-small;\\">.&nbsp;</span></font></span><font class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" face=\\"arial\\"><span class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" style=\\"font-size: x-small;\\">Understanding plasma is important because when\r\nsolar flares erupt, ejections of plasma can wipe out satellite systems and\r\nbring down the power grid.</span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<pre><p><span style=\\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\\"><span class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" style=\\"line-height: 18px; \\"><font class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" face=\\"arial\\"><span class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" style=\\"font-size: x-small;\\">2.&nbsp;</span></font></span></span><font class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" face=\\"arial\\"><span class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" style=\\"font-size: x-small;\\">Mr. Watts has been building a machine that will illuminate the mechanisms underlying solar flares. A bigger machine was made by Mr. Gekelman to study waves of plasma.</span></font></p></pre>\r\n\r\n<pre><p><span style=\\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\\"><span class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" style=\\"line-height: 18px; \\"><font class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" face=\\"arial\\"><span class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" style=\\"font-size: x-small;\\">3. &nbsp;</span></font></span></span><font class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" face=\\"arial\\"><span class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" style=\\"font-size: x-small;\\">Understanding solar flares is important because experts can predict when the next solar flare will be and take precautions to protect against them.</span></font></p></pre>\r\n\r\n<pre><p><span style=\\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\\"><span class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" style=\\"line-height: 18px; \\"><font class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" face=\\"arial\\"><span class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" style=\\"font-size: x-small;\\">4.&nbsp;</span></font></span></span><font class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" face=\\"arial\\"><span class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" style=\\"font-size: x-small;\\">Plasma is used frequently in nuclear energy and when the fossil fuels are gone, plasma can replace it.</span></font></p></pre>\r\n\r\n<pre><p><span style=\\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\\"><span class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" style=\\"line-height: 18px; \\"><font class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" face=\\"arial\\"><span class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" style=\\"font-size: x-small;\\">5. &nbsp;</span></font></span></span><font class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" face=\\"arial\\"><span class=\\"Apple-style-span\\" style=\\"font-size: x-small;\\">Plasma is necessary knowledge because plasma makes up ninety-nine percent of the visible stuff in the universe. Also, the knowledge can help protect us if necessary.</span></font></p></pre>\r\n\r\n<!--EndFragment-->', '2009-10-04 17:54:20'),
(675, 284, 49, 0, '<font size=\\"2\\"><span style=\\"font-family: georgia;\\">1) The understanding of Plasma is important to the communications field because when solar flares they can wipe of satellite systems and people lose power. Scientists can study the flares, plasma, and magnetic fields to undertstand better and maybe predict the flares.&nbsp; They may also serve as a new energy source.</span></font><br><br><span style=\\"font-family: georgia;\\">2) Mr. Watts &amp; Mr. Gekelman made a machine that they hope will help to illuminate the mechanisms beneath solar flares A large 18 foot long machine, surrounded with electromagnetic coils.<br><br>3) Understanding solar flares is important because the relationship between magnetic fields and plasmas is very important.&nbsp; They have to know that plasma can generate a electrical current. <br><br>4) If fossil fuels are depleted, plasma could serve for nuclear fussion and nuclear fusion power plants can use plasma if they know everything about plasma. <br><br>5) I think it really is important. It\\''s like working with a highly reactive chemical, you need to know everything about it so nothing goes wrong. Same with Plasma, you have to know so much more then just plasma itself. You need to study flares, magnetic fields,&nbsp; and even understand satellites.<br></span>', '2009-10-04 18:04:42'),
(676, 348, 51, 0, '*sigh* Okay, here\\''s my second attempt at getting this stupid thing in. It\\''ll be a lot shorter than the first one.<br><br>1) Understanding plasma is important to the communications field because solar winds can sometimes knock out connections and leave people without service. Some can even damage phone lines.<br><br>2) Mr. Watts helped people by making a machine that created a sort or aurora in a bottle and observes how it acts. Mr. Gekelman helped by building another machine with a lot less background noise so that he could see the natural ways plasma moves. His interest especially is Alven waves.<br><br>3) Understanding solar flares is important because it can better prepare us before something bad happens to our technology - our phones and computers and stuff, more specifically.<br><br>4) In the future, when fossil fuels are all used up, nuclear fusion might be the only way we can get power, so to be able to do that effectively, we need to know a lot about plasmas.<br><br>5) I think that understanding plasmas better is very important since it could help us find a cleaner alternative to fossil fuels and might even help us prepare for solar flares and solar winds that might dismantle our communications field.<br>', '2009-10-04 18:09:33'),
(677, 369, 48, 0, '<P>1:&nbsp; the understanding is important because some solar flares are interfering with and destroying satellites in outer space.</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P>2:&nbsp; Watts and Gekelman both made machines that can replicate plasma.</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P>3:&nbsp; Understanding solar flare is important because they can cause massive damage to communication systems throughout the world with their ensuing solar winds.</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P>4:&nbsp; Plasma would supply us with a constant and endless fuel that could be harnessed as long as we have machines to create plasma.</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P>5:&nbsp; I think plasma research would reap multiple benefits in our society today, considering how it could bolster our fuel economy and create a consistent source of energy.&nbsp; It would also help the scientific field in understanding what surrounds the biggest star in our solar system, along with the others.&nbsp; Research could also aide in the awareness of solar flares and their recurring solar winds, and a protection from these dangerous occurences can be made, which can bring down entire power grids.&nbsp; It would also not hurt to have more knowledge of a fourth form of matter on top of everything else.<BR></P>', '2009-10-04 18:09:38'),
(678, 375, 47, 0, '<P>1. Understanding plasma is important because when solar flares erupt, massive ejections of plasma(solar wind) can wipe out satellite systems and bring down power grids.</P>\r\n<P>2. Mr. Watts has been building a machine that he hopes will help usto better understand the underlying mechanisms of solar flares and Mr. Gekelman is an expert at generating plasma structures so he can study wave patterns that would otherwise not occur, he also produces detaiiled images of the waves.</P>\r\n<P>3.&nbsp;Studying waves is&nbsp;important because&nbsp;Alven waves in particular are thought to contribute to the heating of the sun\\''s corona and may also have something to do with the forming density striations in the ionosphere.<BR>4. Plasmas offer a view into the inner workings of stars, and scientists may be able to use hot plasmas as a clean and endless fusion power, which would have an extremly good affect on our economy.</P>\r\n<P>5. Improved knowledge of plasma would be necessary and helpful. It has the power to save us money and fossil fuels in the future.</P>', '2009-10-04 18:25:31'),
(679, 378, 51, 0, '<P><BR><FONT face=verdana>1.&nbsp;because if<FONT>&nbsp;solar flares erupt&nbsp;it will knock out&nbsp;satellite systems and bring down power grids.</FONT></FONT></P>\r\n<P><FONT face=verdana></FONT>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P><FONT face=verdana>2.Mr. Watts is &nbsp;building a machine that will help to illuminate the mechanisms underlying solar flares, Mr. Gekelman is building a larger machine than Mr. Watts</FONT></P>\r\n<P><FONT face=verdana></FONT>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P><FONT face=verdana>3. because if solar flares erupt charged particles are flung into space forming solar wind, which could destroy Earths magnetic field</FONT></P>\r\n<P><FONT face=verdana></FONT>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P><FONT face=verdana>4. if &nbsp;fossil fuels&nbsp;are depleted then&nbsp;nuclear fusion might be our only alternative for energy</FONT></P>\r\n<P><FONT face=verdana></FONT>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P><FONT face=verdana>5. Yes, because plasma is very powerful and can effect lives in a drastic way.</FONT></P>', '2009-10-04 18:47:30'),
