(740, 296, 58, 0, '&nbsp; <span style=\\"font-weight: bold;\\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Pick-An-Element:Lead</span><br><font style=\\"font-family: comic sans ms;\\" size=\\"2\\" face=\\"Arial,Helvetica,Geneva,Swiss,SunSans-Regular\\"><span style=\\"font-family: comic sans ms;\\">Bassam Shakhashiri wrote an this article about lead. Since Bassam was a little boy we has always been interested in lead. When he was a little boy he use to collect this ancient coins made with lead. It was not until he got into college that he started learning more about lead. He learned that lead </span>has more than two dozen radioactive isotopes, </font><font style=\\"font-family: comic sans ms;\\" size=\\"2\\" face=\\"Arial,Helvetica,Geneva,Swiss,SunSans-Regular\\">and is a major component of automobile batteries, that it was widely used in paint, and he </font><font style=\\"font-family: comic sans ms;\\" size=\\"2\\" face=\\"Arial,Helvetica,Geneva,Swiss,SunSans-Regular\\">that\r\neven in ancient times, some physicians believed that lead was\r\npoisonous, but it continued to be used in medicines and cosmetics until\r\nthe 20th century. Lead is used in leaded glasses like for computers and </font><font style=\\"font-family: comic sans ms;\\" size=\\"2\\" face=\\"Arial,Helvetica,Geneva,Swiss,SunSans-Regular\\">lead is the best material for nuclear radiation shielding and allows for the safe operation of CAT scan. Lead is located in the 6 group, 6 row, and 6 peirod. Lead is a metal and is mostly found in </font><font style=\\"font-family: comic sans ms;\\" size=\\"2\\" face=\\"Arial,Helvetica,Geneva,Swiss,SunSans-Regular\\">Wisconsin. A man once told Bassam that lead was mentioned many times in the bible and thought to be the oldest metal. Lead is also </font><font size=\\"2\\" face=\\"Arial,Helvetica,Geneva,Swiss,SunSans-Regular\\"><span style=\\"font-family: comic sans ms;\\">poisonous. Lead is usually found combined with other elements.</span><br></font>', '2009-10-11 12:36:46'),
(741, 367, 55, 0, 'Jora Zaidi<br>Hollis<br>Chemistry 2nd<br>October 11, 2009<br><div style=\\"text-align: center;\\">Cesium (Cs)<br></div><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Richard Kaner is a professor of chemistry and biochemistry at the University of California. Professor\r\nKaner wrote the essay \\"Cesium,\\" due to his enjoyment of conducting\r\nexperiments with the element. Cesium is used for experimentation, to\r\nobserve its reactions with other elements. The location of the element\r\nis in group one, the alkali metals, and period six. Normally, the\r\nelement is found combined with rocks, soil, and dust in low amounts.\r\nApart from the state Cesium is normally found in, it is a metal. In\r\n1860, Cesium was the first element to be discovered using spectroscopic\r\nmeans by Robert W. Bunsen and Gustav R. Kirchhoff. In normal exposure quantities, Cesium is explosive. Cesium is found combined with rocks, soil, and dirt, and is extracted by chemical means. The essay, written by Professor Richard Kaner, gave a helpful insight on the element Cesium. <br>', '2009-10-11 12:53:23'),
(742, 367, 55, 0, 'Jora Zaidi<br>Hollis<br>Chemistry 2nd<br>October 11, 2009<br><div style=\\"text-align: center;\\">Cesium (Cs)<br></div><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nRichard Kaner is a professor of chemistry and biochemistry at the\r\nUniversity of California. Professor\r\nKaner wrote the essay \\"Cesium,\\" due to his enjoyment of conducting\r\nexperiments with the element. Cesium is used for experimentation to\r\nobserve its reactions with other elements. The location of the element\r\nis in group one, the alkali metals, and period six. Normally, the\r\nelement is found combined with rocks, soil, and dust in low amounts.\r\nApart from the state Cesium is normally found in, it is a metal. In\r\n1860, Cesium was the first element to be discovered using spectroscopic\r\nmeans by Robert W. Bunsen and Gustav R. Kirchhoff. In normal exposure\r\nquantities, the element is explosive. Cesium is found in the free state combined with rocks,\r\nsoil, and dirt, and can be extracted through chemical means. The essay written by Professor Richard Kaner was in-depth, and resourceful in providing information.<br><br><span style=\\"font-weight: bold;\\">* Mrs. Hollis: <span style=\\"font-weight: bold;\\">My last post was a rough draft, and submitted by accident, so I am making a second post. </span></span><br>', '2009-10-11 13:06:50'),
(743, 404, 57, 0, '<P align=center><STRONG>Copper</STRONG></P>\r\n<P align=center><STRONG></STRONG>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P dir=ltr style=\\"MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px\\" align=left>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; George M. Whitesides of Harvard University wrote this article on copper. He did not have a natural interest in copper though. He actually planned on doing gold organometallic chemistry. However, his research director suggested that he research copper rather than gold, as it is cheaper and would be far more interesting. After some research,&nbsp;George&nbsp;had already inherited a great interest in copper because of its strange and unknown attributes.</P>\r\n<P dir=ltr style=\\"MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px\\" align=left>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Copper is a crucial element in our lives. It is the most widely-used conductor of all of the elements, it is used in Sterling Silver and is one of the main components of bronze. It is also a commonly-used catalyst. </P>\r\n<P dir=ltr style=\\"MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px\\" align=left>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Copper is the 29th element&nbsp;on the periodic table. It\\''s an outer transition metal located in row 4, group 11. It&nbsp;is a solid in its natural state, and it is classified as a metal. &nbsp;Copper is one of few elements that are found in large quantities in nature. It tends to be fairly reactive and is often found in the form of salts.&nbsp;In its natural state, copper is not dangerous to humans. </P>\r\n<P dir=ltr style=\\"MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px\\" align=left>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Copper is often found as an ore, but it is typically not binded to other elements. Copper salts are easily separated into usable elements, so mining copper is a fairly simple task.</P>\r\n<P dir=ltr style=\\"MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px\\" align=left>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P dir=ltr style=\\"MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px\\" align=left>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </P>\r\n<P align=left><STRONG></STRONG>&nbsp;</P>', '2009-10-11 13:37:26'),
