(750, 253, 54, 0, 'TITANIUM<br><br>This essay is written by Thomas M. Connelly Jr from Dupont. Hes interested in titanium because its closely linked to the development of industries that improve our lives. <font style=\\"font-family: arial;\\" face=\\"Arial,Helvetica,Geneva,Swiss,SunSans-Regular\\" size=\\"2\\">Titanium\\''s\r\ncombination of high strength-to-weight and corrosion resistance, provides tremendous performance enhancements\r\ncompared with more traditional metals used in structural applications. Its located on the 4th row, 22nd group. Its a transition metal and its a solid at normal state. It was named after llmen lake and mountains of Russia. The reduction of it was released in 1950. it is not dangerous at normal exposure to it. It is found as a white pigment named titania. You have to mix titania and sulfuric acid and it creates a metal, Titanium. <br></font>', '2009-10-11 16:01:51'),
