(752, 370, 55, 0, '<P>James Bomba </P>\r\n<P>October 11<BR></P>\r\n<P align=center><U><STRONG>Mercury(Hg)</STRONG></U></P>\r\n<P align=center>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P align=left>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Rudy M.&nbsp;Baum is the writer that&nbsp;wrote this&nbsp;essay on mercury and attended Duke University. Mercury is the only metal that remains a liquid at room temperature and it is a very toxic metal at any exposure quanities, even the acient people knew that. As toxic as it is may be compounds of&nbsp;mercury have been used as disinfectants for&nbsp;centuries. Mercury is located in group 12 and the 6th group. A mercury thermometer has more gravitas then one filled with&nbsp;red liquid.&nbsp;The essay doesnt state where mercury is normally found.</P>', '2009-10-11 16:15:20'),
