(762, 400, 54, 0, '<P><FONT size=5><EM><U>NEON</U></EM> </FONT></P>\r\n<P>Neil Bartlett University of California, Berkeley, he is intrested in the two compound gas. The most commonly known use of neon is in neon signs, and is a high voltage indicator. Also when combined with helium it can form a laser. Neon is located in group 18 period 2. Neon is a nonmetal. Neon was discovered by Sir William Ramsay and Morris Travers in 1898 shortly after the discovery of krypton. Neon is a stable gas but when inhaled can cause suffocation and when it is in a liquid state it can cause frost bite if it touches skin. Neon is found in the atmosphere.<BR></P>', '2009-10-12 11:49:06');
