gineering and\r\nTechnology write about the element arsenic. He says that as a boy, he knew it\r\nto be a homeopathic medicine. He found out it was a poison, but when used in\r\nsmall doses, it can build up resistance to the common cold, asthma, coughs, and\r\nother diseases. Those aren’t the only uses for it though. It is commonly used\r\ntoday for weed killers, insecticides, and solid-state doping agents. It is the\r\n33 element, group 15 row 4. It is a metalloid, and it is most commonly found in\r\nthe groundwater of 3<sup>rd</sup> world countries. <span style=\\"\\">&nbsp;</span>This is why the scientific community has been\r\nso captivated by the element. Being the 20<sup>th</sup> most abundant element\r\nin the earth’s crust, it is contaminating the drinking water of less fortunate\r\ncountries who must drink ground water. Lethal amounts of exposure to Arsenic\r\ncan be observed by the senses of sight, taste, and smell. </p>', '2009-10-13 20:37:18'),
