(809, 320, 55, 0, '<P align=center>Calcium (Ca)</P>\r\n<P align=center>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P align=left>This essay was written by <A name=Anchor-Sture-23067></A><FONT face=Helvetica><FONT size=2><STRONG>Sture Forsén,&nbsp;</STRONG>and he first came into \\"contact\\" with Calcium during his graduate&nbsp;studies, and during his&nbsp;<FONT face=Tahoma><FONT face=Arial>nuclear magnetic resonance spectroscopy&nbsp;of nuclei, he used Calcium. Calcium is commonly found in the Earth\\''s crust, and used to \\"help build strong bones,\\" or so goes the milk commercials! Calcium is an alkaline Earth metal, and is found on the second group and the fourth period. Calcium is commonly found in a solid state, and is a metal. It proved difficult for scientists to isolate calcium, it was not until 1808 that they managed to do so! Calcium is not normally found in its elemental state, but it is commonly found in the human body!</FONT></FONT></FONT></FONT><BR></P>', '2009-10-13 20:57:23'),
