(2046, 558, 168, 0, '<BR>Uuuurgh. I can''t believe I forgot to give my repsonse to this. Better late than never I hope. But when it came to the movie Earth 2100, I guess I can say that I was very much surprised. There was an extremely scary realistic touch to this and there is now I know, in this worst-case scenario, that if we don''t do anything to stop all the wrong we have done onto Mother Nature, she''ll come back and hit us. This movie has helped me see that there is so much more to the solutions we try to have, such as the chemical that in Lucy''s world they put in to keep the radiation of the sun''s rays to keep out ended up dissolving the Earth''s Ozone layer, also have consequences to them. That made me question, are the unintended consequences recieved from the solutions we try to make worse or worth it when it comes to saving our world? The movie also made me very mad, seeing how many humans are just so stubborn and selfish. It angers me and if we humans weren''t as stubborn and as selfish as we are, the world probably wouldn''t be where it is today and Lucy''s worst-case-scenario story would be where we are today. That is basically it that I thought, but this movie really made me think, and really hope that we humans begin to step out of our box of "everything-is-us," and do something to save the Mother Nature which has nurtured us and kept us and so many other species alive for so many years. It would be terrible if one of Mother Nature''s creation destroyed the caring force which has kept it alive for so long.', '2010-09-01 18:27:18'),
