(2064, 587, 170, 0, '<i><font class="Apple-style-span" face="arial">Ex Situ</font></i><font class="Apple-style-span" face="arial">&nbsp;and <i>In situ</i>&nbsp;conservation of Panthera Once (jaguar)&nbsp;</font><div><font class="Apple-style-span" face="arial">By Kyla Cullinane and Dallas Koch</font></div><div><font class="Apple-style-span" face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font class="Apple-style-span" face="arial">The jaguar is endangered because of habitat depeletion and hunting by ranchers as a pest species due to the jaguar killing livestock. The jaguar''s range is from northern Mexico to southern South America concentrated in Brazil.&nbsp;</font></div><div><font class="Apple-style-span" face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font class="Apple-style-span" face="arial">There are two methods in conserving the jaguar,&nbsp;<i style="margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; ">Ex Situ</i>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<i style="margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; ">In situ. Ex situ</i><span style="margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; ">&nbsp;includes the introduction of zoos and botanical gardens. The strengths of <i>ex situ</i>&nbsp;are:</span></font></div><div><ul><li><font class="Apple-style-span" face="arial">Since the jaguar has such a large range, it is cheaper and uses less resources to conserve the Jaguars in zoos and seed banks.</font></li><li><font class="Apple-style-span" face="arial">Promotes public awareness/education of the endangerment of the Jaguar.</font></li></ul></div><div><font class="Apple-style-span" face="arial">However, the limitations of <i>ex situ</i>&nbsp;are:</font></div><div><ul><li><font class="Apple-style-span" face="arial">Most funding is put towards the <i>in situ</i>&nbsp;conservation, and little towards <i>ex situ</i></font></li><li><font class="Apple-style-span" face="arial">little sucess in captive breeding of Jaguars</font></li></ul></div><div><font class="Apple-style-span" face="arial">The other method of conservation is <i>In Situ. </i>This method includes the conservation of the jaguars in their natural habitat through legislation and national reserves. The strengths of this method are:</font></div><div><ul><li><font class="Apple-style-span" face="arial">Researches the jaguar inside\r\nits natural habitat</font></li><li><font class="Apple-style-span" face="arial">First hand experience of the\r\ndepletion on habitat and its effects on the jaguar</font></li><li><font class="Apple-style-span" face="arial">Promotes habitat\r\nrehabilitation in the local area, thus a bigger impact and more chance of action</font></li></ul><font class="Apple-style-span" face="arial">However, the limitations of <i>in situ</i>&nbsp;are:</font></div><div><ul><li><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: Arial; ">Large habitat range and\r\ncannot be studied at once</span></li><li><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: Arial; "></span><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: Arial; ">Very difficult to monitor\r\nbecause of its solitary, cryptic, and nocturnal habits</span></li><li><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: Arial; "></span><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: Arial; ">Main reason for endangerment\r\nis that jaguars eat cattle and to ranchers they are a pest species. Without keeping\r\nthe jaguars captive, they cannot be completely protected from extermination by\r\nranchers under national and international laws. It is not possible to enforce\r\nlaws without segregating the jaguar population in captivity.&nbsp;</span></li></ul></div><div><span style="margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; "><font class="Apple-style-span" face="arial"><br></font></span></div><div><font class="Apple-style-span" face="arial">We recommend that the best way to conserve the Jaguar is through <i>in situ</i>&nbsp;conservation. This is due to the fact that there is more funding for <i>in situ</i>&nbsp;and that studies have shown that the Jaguar has not successfully bred in captivity due to unknown factors. Because of this fact it is much more useful to use resources in an area that can successfully help the jaguars which is in <i>in situ</i>&nbsp;conservation.&nbsp;</font></div><div><font class="Apple-style-span" face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font class="Apple-style-span" face="arial">Sources used:&nbsp;</font></div><div><font class="Apple-style-span" face="arial"><a href="http://www.procarnivoros.org.br/pdfs/Reproductive_seasonality_in_the_jaguar.pdf">http://www.procarnivoros.org.br/pdfs/Reproductive_seasonality_in_the_jaguar.pdf</a></font></div><div><font class="Apple-style-span" face="arial"></font><font class="Apple-style-span" face="arial"><a href="http://www.waza.org/en/zoo/visit-the-zoo/cats-1254385523/panthera-onca">http://www.waza.org/en/zoo/visit-the-zoo/cats-1254385523/panthera-onca</a></font></div><div><font class="Apple-style-span" face="arial"></font><font class="Apple-style-span" face="arial"><a href="http://www.iucnredlist.org/apps/redlist/details/15953/0">http://www.iucnredlist.org/apps/redlist/details/15953/0</a></font></div><div><a href="http://www.jaguarnetwork.org/index.htm">http://www.jaguarnetwork.org/index.htm</a></div><div><a href="http://www.ekonoiz.com/Eco_Projects/Jaguar_Conservation/OncaProject.htm">http://www.ekonoiz.com/Eco_Projects/Jaguar_Conservation/OncaProject.htm</a></div>', '2010-11-01 09:35:17'),
